	<!-- custom: these are the very bad tiles management knobs/tunables in AIFoundValue::evaluate function. Tweaking these allows to change the code we added that tells AI how very bad tiles are valued. Changing it will (at least should but anyways etc) change AI settling preferences and recommended sites in UI as well if i'm not mistaken anyways etc. Are accounted as very bad tiles (check if not updated in code anyways etc), in BFC (excluding home plot (i.e. plot where we settle/found/plant our city anyways etc)):
		- peak tiles
		- ice cap tiles
		- desert tiles that are not hill and have no bonus
		- snow (i.e. ice sheet) tiles that are not hill and have no bonus
	Start phase is before our first city is planted/settled/founded but anyways etc.
	Note: these max tolerated tiles defines are checked with a >, not >=, so if you choose a value for example of 3, it means 4+ triggers the effect anyways etc
	-->
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_MAX_TOLERATED_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILES_START</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>2</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_MAX_TOLERATED_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILES_LATER</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>3</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<!-- custom: the higher this positive number is, the more we penalize and think this tile is very very bad, for example 75 would mean a harsher evaluation of this tile and thus likeliness to avoid the city site that has this tile in BFC than say 50 if i'm not mistaken but anyways etc. This value is multiplied by the number of bad tiles if we are past the strict max tolerated threshold, for example if we have 4 very bad tiles in BFC and we are at start game and the start very bad base value is 100, the currently evaluated city site that has these in BFC would have a penalty in value (and thus likeliness to consider it our best site to settle) of 4 * (-100) = - 400 to its value which is as of now a bit more than what iron would give for example so quite big but anyways etc. -->
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_BASE_VALUE_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILE_START</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>-100</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<DefineName>SAS_EVALUATE_BASE_VALUE_NOT_HOME_VERY_BAD_TILE_LATER</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>-75</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>



